
Phase 1: Project Setup & Environment Configuration

- Initialize Git and create GitHub repo
- Setup folder structure (client + server)
- Install dependencies (React, Node, Express, MongoDB, etc.)
- Setup `.env` files for sensitive configs
- Connect backend to MongoDB using Mongoose


Phase 2: Authentication & Authorization

- User Registration & Login functionality
- JWT-based authentication
- Secure user routes (e.g., adding books, admin panel)
- Role-based access (e.g., admin vs regular user)



Phase 3: Core Bookstore Features

- Add, Edit, Delete books (CRUD)
- Book details page
- Search & filter functionality
- Book categories & ratings
- Pagination (optional)


Phase 4: Creating sell your book section 
- Add a admin dashboard section there
- Two separate section one for sign in options
- Another for future Advancement




Phase 5: UI/UX Enhancement & Deployment

- Final UI design with Tailwind / Custom CSS
- Responsive layout for all devices
- Error handling and validation
- Deploy frontend (e.g., Vercel) & backend (e.g., Render, Railway)

